  <p>
    Pupils at The Independent School of Jakarta celebrated Halloween with an afternoon of costumes, dancing, and treats at the school's annual Halloween Disco. From spooky outfits to creative face paint, the event brought the ISJ community together in true festive spirit.
  </p>

  <p>
    The afternoon was filled with music, laughter, and plenty of energy as children from across the school took to the dance floor. It was a chance for pupils, parents, and teachers to enjoy a lighter moment together and mark one of the most popular dates in the school calendar.
  </p>

